		<td><b>Re: Development/Hacking source and binary attachments.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ditto. I attach things here that I think will be single-version, but post links to things I might update. Outdated versions lingering around sometimes misleads someone from finding the current version.<br /><br />Perhaps a solution is to attach the current version to the post, and also link to the version on one's site. Others can attach newer versions to the thread if desired. Taking this further, ideally we'd archive everything people post on nesdev. One barrier is the inability to organize the files here or even list them, or filter out the less-significant things. Writing this I can imagine the kinds of tools that should be available for doing things like this effortlessly, e.g. &quot;Oh, someone uploaded a file, click, type 'tool to check bla bla' &lt;return&gt;&quot; and it's added to some repository without further effort.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

