	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For one thing, phpBB 2 didn't support attachments at all. For another, a lot of boards like this are configured to hide attachments from anonymous visitors and unconfirmed accounts, to intentionally break inbound links to downloadable files on grounds of &quot;bandwidth theft&quot;, etc. NESdev currently isn't configured this way, but boards that are configured this way have spoiled the attachment feature for people who want to make downloadable files available to the public.<br /><br />I'm liking blargg's suggestion.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
